  "riddle": "**1.** Start your journey by unearthing the tale of the eldest daughter of a pioneering missionary couple. Discover how many young adventurers, bearing their surname, embarked on an Oriental voyage in 1866.\n\n**2.** With the number you’ve found, employ some arithmetic wizardry: determine the sum of the unique prime numbers that secretly compose it.\n\n**3.** Seek a historical faith that split into branches major and varied. Count these divisions to proceed.\n\n**4.** Envision an eastern capital where the dragon once roared; measure its height above the sea to continue the quest.\n\n**5.** Picture an immense oriental city, known for commerce and lights. How high does its skyline rise?\n\n**6.** Now, once more calculate the soaring height of this bustling eastern hub, using the best cartographer’s tools.\n\n**7.** Within sight of this metropolis, how many sanctuaries of knowledge and heritage can be found?\n\n**8.** Combine your discoveries from clues 6 and 7 by pondering the riddle: what is the absolute contrast between these two troves of knowledge?\n\n**9.** Contemplate the towers from clue 5, searching for the solitude of the next alchemical integer.\n\n**10.** Gaze skyward and consider the universal language of the stars. How many tongues tell its story?\n\n**11.** Reflect on ancient wisdom at the cradle of learning. Count the chapters of knowledge inscribed within.\n\n**12.** Meditate on the distilled essence: sum the individual units that comprise clue 11’s wisdom.\n\n**13.** Journey to the land where magi once walked and discern how many dialects tell of the eternal flame.\n\n**14.** In a land once touched by Greek sages, find the altitude of its resting gods.\n\n**15.** Seek the air that sustains life and wonder what portion is claimed by the inert colorless giant.\n\n**16.** Look to a culture that mapped the celestial with essays in sundry tongues. How many languages convey their celestial odyssey?\n\n**17.** Travel to an island nation steeped in saffron robes. What fraction of its people walk the path of Dharma in the year of the swiftly approaching future?\n\n**18.** Finally, synthesize your efforts where the sun rises and sets. Use the magic of the digital root to distill the past reflections of clues 11 and 16 into a singular essence. What number remains? This is your ultimate answer.",
